5.10 We recommended that Management take the following actions to address the identified deficiencies:
5.10.a Immediately revert/remit the ₱7,100,000.00 to the appropriate fund source or to the National Treasury, in compliance with COA Circular No. 2012-003;
5.10.b Immediately discontinue the implementation of the ERP funded from public resources, and expedite the collection of outstanding loans through salary deduction or other lawful and enforceable means;
5.10.c Conduct a legal review and initiate the repeal or amendment of Municipal Ordinance No. 04, Series of 2022, considering its inconsistency with national laws governing the use of public funds and the absence of enabling authority to operate a lending program;
5.10.d Explore legally permissible alternatives for providing financial assistance to employees, such as facilitating access to credit through the Government Service Insurance System (GSIS), other government financial institutions (GFIs), or accredited employee cooperatives, in line with existing laws, policies, and guidelines; and
5.10.e Henceforth, enforce stricter internal controls to ensure that collected disallowed amounts are promptly remitted and/or reverted in accordance with government regulations.

3.8 	We have recommended and the Municipal Accountant agreed to:
Reclassify the amount of ₱129,184.90 to the Due to BIR account and initiate procedures to recover the overpaid taxes from BIR, if possible;
Improve the coordination among its staff in the withholding, remittance and recording of taxes to ensure that all remittances are cross-checked against taxes withheld in the accounting records regularly before they are processed;
Initiate the verification, analysis, validation and reconciliation of the long outstanding balance of the receivable from DA and PTA in the Due from NGAs account with the books of the agencies concerned to establish the legitimacy of the receivable and if found to be contrary, seek other remedial measures; and
Justify why the overpaid taxes be not disallowed in audit.

7.8 	We have recommended and Management agreed to ensure the following:
The Municipal Treasurer to closely supervise and monitor the remittances of collections through strict enforcement of Section 29 of the NGAS Manual for LGUs, Volume I and impose appropriate penal sanctions to revenue collectors who repeatedly fail to remit on time, if necessary;
All Collecting Officers to submit their collections daily and intact as prescribed in Section 29 of the NGAS Manual for LGUs, Volume I;
The Municipal Treasurer to consider not issuing additional accountable forms to collecting officers unless collections pertaining to the accountable forms previously issued them are remitted intact or an inventory of any unused accountable form had been diligently prepared; and
For field collectors, where collections are minimal and daily remittance or deposit is costly and impractical, to remit/submit their collections at least once a week, or as soon as the collection reaches ₱5,000.00.

We have recommended that Management:

enforce the provisions stated in the MOA with the Mayoyao Weavers Association;
…

We have recommended and Management agreed:

that the Municipal Accountant impose the 10% Retention Money from progress payments of all infrastructure projects in accordance with the guidelines in RA No. 9184;

to require contractors to post Performance Security, in whatever form, with validity period covering contract signing until date of final acceptance;

to require the contractors to post Warranty Security, in whatever form, as required in RA No. 9184;

to strengthen the monitoring and inspection mechanisms of the MLGU, and proceed with the issuance of the Certificate of Completion after thorough evaluation of the projects as required, and the Certificate of Final Acceptance after one (1) year from the date of Certificate of Completion to cover the defects liability period; and

to make officials concerned liable incase defects in projects not imposed with required warranties, and where contractors refuse to rectify.

We have recommended and Management agreed that:

the Municipal Engineer ensure that infrastructure projects are completed within the target period of completion;


the Municipal Development Council review and re-evaluate the feasibility of long overdue 20% MDF projects and revert the appropriations of those no longer feasible (overtaken by time and the changes in the present needs of beneficiaries) for implementation of other priority development projects;


the MDRRM Council re-appropriate to DRRM-related programs those administrative expenses funded under MDRRMF (Annex H), and the MDRRM Officer expedite the implementation of the programs under the MDRRMF capital outlays identified to reduce and manage disaster risks; and


the Heads of Office concerned, (i) expedite the implementation of fund transfers in accordance with the purpose specified in the relative Memorandum of Agreement (MOA), if still possible; or (ii) return to the source agency the unutilized/idle fund transfers, if no provision in the MOA for the use of remaining balances.

We have recommended that Management:
;
require the GAD Focal Point to administer the HGDG test on the LGU’s GAD PPAs in the preparation of Accomplishment Report, as basis for determining the actual expenditure that can be attributed to the GAD Budget;

administer the HGDG test on its PPAs for CY 2017, the results of which shall be the basis in estimating the cost of gender mainstreaming and GAD Budget; 

if and when necessary, conduct a training program on the HGDG for the incoming year and seek assistance of a gender analysis expert in the use of and/administration of the HGDG; and

We have recommended that
Management:

submit to the SA and ATL a complete list of all government projects/programs/activities that are on-going as of the beginning of CY 2015 and those that are to be implemented during CY 2015, and, henceforth, comply with Section 2.1 of COA Circular No. 2013-004;



inform the SA and ATL within ten (10) days after the award of the infrastructure project or before the start of the program/activity that the appropriate project signboards and/or public notices are already posted during CY 2015, and, henceforth, comply with Section 3.1 of COA Circular No. 2013-004;
